\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
1.
 Purpose
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The purpose of this policy is to define the lifecycle,
 cadence,
 responsibilities,
 and mechanisms for reviewing,
 updating,
 and reauthorizing official IT policies within the Elko County Information Operations Department.
 Its goal is to ensure all policies remain current,
 enforceable,
 and aligned with legal,
 operational,
 and institutional realities.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
2.
 Scope
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy applies to all formal Information Technology policies governed by the Elko County Information Operations Department (the "Policy Manual").
 It does not apply to draft procedures,
 working documents,
 or informal guidance.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
3.
 Roles and Responsibilities
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
IT Director
\series default
:
 Shall oversee annual reviews,
 approve internal revisions,
 and issue emergency changes when operational integrity is at risk.
 Shall ensure review records are available for audit.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
County Manager
\series default
:
 Grants final approval for standard policy updates,
 governance changes,
 and formal exceptions.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
County Commission
\series default
:
 Approves policies requiring legal ratification,
 funding appropriation,
 or significant changes to County governance structure.
\end_layout

