\lang english
6.
 Policy Statement
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.1 Review Cadence
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
To ensure continued relevance and compliance,
 all policies shall undergo the following review cycles:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Annual Internal Review
\series default
:
 The IT Director or designated Policy Owners shall conduct an annual internal review of each policy to evaluate compliance,
 technical accuracy,
 and workforce awareness.
 This review supports 
\series bold
NIST SP 800-53 Rev.
 5 PM-1
\series default
 and 
\series bold
PM-2
\series default
 and 
\series bold
CJIS Security Policy v6.0 Section 5.1.1.6
\series default
 by ensuring program leadership actively evaluates and maintains the policy framework.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Biennial Resanction
\series default
:
 The IT Director shall coordinate biennial resanction of the Policy Manual with the County Manager and,
 where required,
 the County Commission.
 This resanction reaffirms institutional support,
 risk tolerance,
 and funding alignment for the IT governance framework.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Ad Hoc Reviews
\series default
:
 Policy Owners shall initiate ad hoc reviews when triggered by:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Regulatory or legal changes (e.g.,
 FBI CJIS Security Policy updates).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Internal or external audit findings.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Major incidents or critical system events requiring post-mortem policy adjustment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Significant organizational changes (e.g.,
 departmental mergers or new mandates).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Significant technology changes (e.g.,
 new platforms,
 major infrastructure shifts).
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.2 Policy Lifecycle and Change Control
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Updates to the Policy Manual shall follow this strict change control workflow:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
\lang english
Identification
\series default
:
 The reviewer or Policy Owner shall identify needed revisions based on the criteria in Section 6.1.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
\lang english
Drafting
\series default
:
 Draft updates shall be prepared in accordance with the formatting standards in Policy 1.04 and the version control requirements in 
\series bold
Appendix 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "app:6.04"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
\lang english
Approval
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The IT Director shall approve technical and operational changes that do not alter governance structures or budget authority.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The County Manager shall approve changes that affect governance constructs,
 decision rights,
 or risk appetite,
 and shall escalate to the County Commission when legal ratification or additional appropriation is required.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
\lang english
Notification
\series default
:
 
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The IT Director shall notify all affected personnel of every approved policy change within five (5) business days.
 Notification shall include an effective date,
 a summary of changes,
 and a link to the authoritative policy record.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
All personnel whose duties are impacted by the change shall complete a documented acknowledgement (electronic or written) within 
\series bold
ten (10) business days
\series default
 of notice.
 Failure to acknowledge does not delay the effective date and constitutes noncompliance.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
\lang english
Publication
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The policy version shall be incremented in accordance with 
\series bold
Appendix 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "app:6.04"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The new version shall be committed to the Authoritative System of Record (LyX/PDF) and synchronized to the System of Engagement (Redmine).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The previous version shall be marked "Obsolete" and archived in accordance with 
\series bold
Appendix 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "app:6.04"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 and applicable retention schedules.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
\lang english
Retirement
\series default
:
 Policies deemed no longer necessary must be formally retired.
 The retirement process requires the same approval level as the policy's original creation.
 Retired policies are removed from active circulation but retained in the archive in accordance with 
\series bold
Appendix 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "app:6.04"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 and applicable retention schedules for legal defensibility.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.3 Emergency Policy Changes
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The IT Director may issue temporary policy amendments ("Technical Directives") when standard policies obstruct legal compliance,
 operational integrity,
 or incident response.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Permissible Scenarios
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
A CJIS,
 HIPAA,
 or statutory compliance deadline requiring immediate action.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Response to a zero-day vulnerability or active threat.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Critical failure affecting escalation,
 access control,
 or procedures.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Constraints
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Must be documented immediately in the Policy Review Tracker.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Must include justification,
 scope,
 and a specific expiration date.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Emergency Deviations established through Technical Directives are subject to the same documentation and exception requirements defined in Section 4.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Automatic Expiration
\series default
:
 Emergency policies expire after 
\series bold
90 calendar days
\series default
.
 Upon expiration,
 the Technical Directive shall either be (a) incorporated into a formally approved policy revision following the process in Section 6.2,
 or (b) explicitly rescinded and documented in the Policy Review Tracker.
 The same or substantially similar emergency policy shall not be re-issued within twelve (12) months of expiration without formal adoption through the standard approval process.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Limitation
\series default
:
 Emergency powers may not be used to alter budget authority or core governance roles defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.06"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.4 Policy Review Tracker
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
All policy review and update activity shall be recorded in the Departmental Knowledge Base (Redmine).
 Policy Owners shall ensure that review and update records for their assigned policies are created and maintained,
 and the IT Director shall ensure these records are available to support internal audits and the maturity scoring process defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.10"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 Required metadata for every update includes:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Policy ID and Title
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Last Review Date and Next Scheduled Review Date
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Responsible Reviewer or Policy Owner
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Review Status (Compliant/Revision Needed/Obsolete)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Associated Work Order or Ticket Reference Link
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Reference to any applicable audit finding,
 incident report,
 or regulatory change.
\end_layout

